# Router delegation

When delegating developer → verifier:

1. **Developer:** Run `make all` once at completion. During development, use incremental commands (`go test ./pkg/...`, `go build`) — do not run full `make all` after every change.
2. **Verifier:** When developer reports `make all` passed, do not re-run full `make all`. Trust that output; focus on plan compliance and spot-checks. Re-run only if developer reported failure or did not run it.

This avoids wasting 75%+ of time on redundant `make` commands in the develop→verify loop.
